        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:2:53:1",
        "relations": null,
        "text": [
          " سَأَلْتُهُ عَنْ طَلَاقِ السَّكْرَانِ فَقَالَ لَا يَجُوزُ وَ لَا كَرَامَةَ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hammad, from Al Halby, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, said, ‘I asked him<sup>asws</sup> about divorce of the intoxicated one, so he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘It is not allowed, and there is no prestige’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "1. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘ Umayr from Hammad from al-Halabiy who has said the following: “I once asked abu ‘ Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, about the divorce of a drunken man. He (the Imam) said, ‘It is not permissible and it is not an honorable thing.”’ "
          ]
        }
