        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:2:53:2",
        "relations": null,
        "text": [
          " لَيْسَ طَلَاقُ السَّكْرَانِ بِشَيْ‏ءٍ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Muhammad Bin Ismail, from Muhammad Bin Al Fuzayl, from Abu Al Sabbah Al Kinany, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘A divorce by the intoxicated one is not with anything’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "2. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from Muhammad ibn ’Isma‘il has narrated from al-Fadl ibn Shadhan from abu al-Sabbah al-Kinaniy who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Divorce of a drunken man does not have any valid effect.’” "
          ]
        }
