        "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:2:53:4",
        "relations": null,
        "text": [
          " سَأَلْتُهُ عَنْ طَلَاقِ السَّكْرَانِ فَقَالَ لَا يَجُوزُ وَ لَا عِتْقُهُ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Humeyd Bin Ziyad, from Ibn Sama’at, from Ibn Rabat and Al Husayn Bin Hashim, from Safwan, altogether from Ibn Muskan, from Al Halby, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, said, ‘I asked him<sup>asws</sup> about a divorce by the intoxicated one, so he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘Not allowed, nor his emancipation (liberation of a slave)’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "4. Humayd ibn Ziyad has narrated from ibn Sama‘ah from ibn Ribat and al-Husayn ibn Hashim from Safwan all from ibn Muskan from al-Halabiy who has said the following: “I once asked abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, about the divorce of a drunken man. He (the Imam) said, ‘It is not permissible as well as his setting free of slaves.’” "
          ]
        }
